metadata.name: Glossolalia #146
metadata.description:
This series is ultimately about catharsis. The compositions can be chaotic and maybe even a little messy, but they also can be vibrant and diverse… which is really what this is trying to celebrate: diversity and expression.

Simply, it’s about the emotions associated with whatever frees you.

Please see the linked fxtext article (on the main project page) for a more in-depth dissection of the concept. It’s less of a technical discussion, and more about the experience of the artist, and how it became linked with the feelings they associate with the art.

In live mode:

For higher resolutions, you can append “&density=2” to the url to double the size, “&density=3” to triple, and so on.
(This is highly recommended.)

To adjust grain, you can append “&grain=##” to the url. 40 is the default, and 0 will remove it completely.

metadata.name: \\Earth Hug// #13
metadata.description:
\\Celebrate the Earth Day with HUGGGs//

How to achieve Peace and Sustainability? How to give the chaos world some hope?
The most simple and the only answer I could think of is 'LOVE'. It flows like water from genuine humanity.
It might sounds like a cliché, but it might be the truth.
Love could be conveyed in various ways, and I think the most powerful one is HUGs.

 Let's give the earth some hugs, not only the earth but also the people around you. and 
Become the light of hope, peace, and love.

- 
Color of the earth and the light would depend on your wallet address.
Drag your mouse and click to find the best spot to cuddle with the earth \(OuO)/ Enjoyyy

metadata.name: CA Monti #49
metadata.description:
As a sequel of previous collection CA Vista but with a completely different approach, CA Monti intends to explore landscape generation through the use of Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.

Press 'S' to download.

metadata.name: CA Panico #238
metadata.description:
Third chapter of the trilogy dedicated to Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.
 
Compared to CA Vista and CA Monti, CA Panico aims to further abstract the concept of landscape using CA rules in a more massive way.

The great variety of CA rules that controls the coloring and textures, noise influence, division into quadrants, chance of having glitches and outages all combined with 25 palettes and 5 different formats means that the outputs will be very varied and peculiar.

Press 'S' to download, you can zoom downloaded output to enjoy all the details.

metadata.name: Skull Village  #45
metadata.description:
In this generative project, you will see a combination of digital art and modern art and fine art, as well as using elements produced through artificial intelligence.

This project is a digital collage and different layers are designed to make it
In this project, there are 14 different Traits, which are many layers under each.
There are a total of 122 different layers that are combined, which makes it less likely that two images are close to each other because only 256 NFTs are randomly minted out of 3,910,952,263,680 different states.
This project is the result of more than 100 hours of effort and therefore this project will be very valuable
In addition, due to the fact that some layers are more special, this project has a rarity


Designed by: @3d_punk
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Tangled #33
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: When we were Kids #5
metadata.description:
When we were kids.

A work that goes back to our childhood.
When I was a kid I loved spending time with my grandmother and parents, we took a lot of walks with them, looked at different houses, spent time in nature, painted and in general were very much involved in the creative component, it was my parents and grandmother who instilled in me a love for creativity.

Probably one of the few things that have survived to these days is my childhood drawings, a little funny, sloppy, but so real and sincere.

In this work I wanted to take me back to those carefree times and remember with what eagerness and zeal I tried every day to learn something new or to go further than before.

None of this would have happened without my family, for which I am truly grateful.

10% of primary sales will be donated to Cure Parkinson's, I hope all children will have a childhood where they can spend time with their loved ones.

Be patient, some variations take a little longer to render.

Press S for Save Canvas as PNG.

By aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.
